TEXT.0: SWE, a comprehensive plasma instrument for the WIND spacecraft,  K.W. Ogilvie, et al., Space Sci. Rev., 71, 55-77, 1995.

TEXT.2: Quality flags are set in the analysis program that generates the KP data.  Previous descriptions of their meaning were out of date.

TEXT.3: Good data is indicated by a quality flag of 0.

TEXT.4: The quality flags for each parameter are given as integers 4 bytes long (integer*4).  The individual 'bits' for each quality value are set (or cleared) in the analysis code by adding (or subtracting) a power of 2 as follows: To set the 1st bit, add 1.  To set the 2nd bit, add 2. To set the 3rd bit, add 4.  To set the 4th bit, add 8, and so on.

TEXT.6: 1    +1     = 3 point parabolic fits to proton peaks were not attempted.

TEXT.7: 2    +2     = non-linear least squares fit was not attempted.

TEXT.8: 3    +4     = 3 point parabolic fits to proton peaks FAILED.

TEXT.9: 4    +8     = non-linear least squares fit FAILED. (Non-linear fit may be reported as good for protons and, at the same time, not good for alphas.)

TEXT.10: 5    +16    = Alpha params not valid for reason that the non-linear least squares fit was done for protons only.  Not enough good energy channels to do simultaneous alpha fit. (This value applies to iqual_core(5) only.)

TEXT.11: 6    +32    = analysis code unable to get good value for spin period.

TEXT.12: 7    +64    = SWE instrument in mode 1 - calibration state.  Key parameters not produced this mode, only in mode 1 - science.

TEXT.13: 8   +128   = 3 point fits done for cup 1 only.  Split collector ratio of currents used to get n/s angle.  Either cup 2 turned off, or cup 2 densities were low indicating noise associated with vibration.

TEXT.14: 9   +256   = fewer than 10 fc_blocks in spectrum. Analysis skipped.

TEXT.15: 10  +512   = Alpha non-linear fit produced values of thermal speed and density that do not seem reasonable.

TEXT.16: 11  +1024   = 3 point parabolic fits to proton peaks done for cup 2 only. Ratio of currents on split collectors used to get n/s angle.  Probably Cup 1 is turned off.

TEXT.17: 12  +2048   = single width windows.  Delta E over E 6/5% instead of the default 13%.

TEXT.19: 14  +8192   = Limited tracking mode scan (Not a full scan)

TEXT.21: Non-linear fits are not done for Key Parameters (KPs), but those parameter values are excellent and should be used to do science; non-linear fits are available, but they have problems which suggest strongly that the KP parameters should be used (see paper by Kasper et al., 'Physics-based tests to identify the accuracy of solar wind ion measurements: A case study with the Wind Faraday Cups', J. Geophys. Res., 111, A03105, doi:101029/2005JA011442. Examples (note that all are even numbers because non-linear fits were not attempted)

TEXT.23: 4098   Tracking mode (4096) full scan  + no non-linear (2)

TEXT.25: See http://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/wind_swe_quality.html for the complete guide to the quality flag values.
